# Google Sign-In + Demo Credential Removal

## Summary
Add Google Sign-In to Login & Register pages with email-based account linking, remove demo credentials, and implement admin login via configurable email list.

## Core Logic: "Same Email = Same Account"

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[User clicks Sign in with Google] --> B[Google returns ID token with email + name]
    B --> C{Email exists in DB?}
    C -->|Yes, Patient| D[Login as that Patient]
    C -->|Yes, Doctor| E[Login as that Doctor]
    C -->|Yes, Admin| F[Login as Admin]
    C -->|No| G{Email in ADMIN_EMAILS?}
    G -->|Yes| H[Create Admin account → Login]
    G -->|No| I[Create Patient account → Login]
    D --> J[Return JWT token]
    E --> J
    F --> J
    H --> J
    I --> J
```

**Key behavior**: If `rahul@example.com` registered manually as a patient, then later does Google Sign-In with the same email → they get **the exact same patient profile** and JWT token. No duplicate accounts.

