## Admin Login Flow

| Method | How it works |
|--------|-------------|
| **Google Sign-In** | If email matches `ADMIN_EMAILS` → login/create as admin |
| **Manual (email+password)** | Standard login against Admin collection with bcrypt password |

`ADMIN_EMAILS` is a comma-separated env var: `maazk8448@gmail.com,another@admin.com`

> [!IMPORTANT]
> You need a **Google OAuth Client ID** for this to work. 
> Go to [Google Cloud Console → Credentials](https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials), create an **OAuth 2.0 Client ID** (Web application type), and add `http://localhost:5173` to "Authorized JavaScript origins".
> I'll add placeholders in `.env` — you just paste your Client ID.

